<Window x:Class="ReasonLivePlayer.Views.HelpDialog"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        Title="Reasonable Live Player — Help" Width="480" Height="540"
        Background="#1E1E1E" Foreground="White"
        WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner" ResizeMode="NoResize"
        ShowInTaskbar="False">
    <Grid Margin="16">
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="*"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>

        <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="13" LineHeight="20">
                <Run FontSize="16" FontWeight="Bold">Reasonable Live Player</Run>
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Overview</Run><LineBreak/>
                RLP automates live set playback in Reason. It opens songs in sequence
                and advances to the next when a MIDI trigger note is received.
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">RLP Setup</Run><LineBreak/>
                1. Click ＋ or drag .reason / .rns files from Explorer into the playlist.<LineBreak/>
                2. Open Settings (⚙) and select your MIDI input device, channel, and trigger note number.<LineBreak/>
                3. The MIDI indicator turns green when connected.<LineBreak/>
                4. Press ▶ to start — RLP opens the first song in Reason.<LineBreak/>
                5. When the trigger note is received, RLP closes the current song and opens the next.
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Usage</Run><LineBreak/>
                • Drag and drop .reason files from Windows Explorer into the playlist.<LineBreak/>
                • Reorder songs by dragging within the list.<LineBreak/>
                • Click the indicator column next to a song while paused to select it as the next song to play.<LineBreak/>
                • Save and load playlists to quickly recall your set order.<LineBreak/>
                • Enable "Load last playlist on startup" in Settings to pick up where you left off.<LineBreak/>
                • Increase the transition delay in Settings if the next song fails to open
                  (especially when a background Reason file is loaded).
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Toolbar Buttons</Run><LineBreak/>
                ▶ / ⏸  Play or pause the playlist<LineBreak/>
                ⏭  Skip to the next song<LineBreak/>
                ＋  Add .reason / .rns files<LineBreak/>
                💾  Save playlist (.rlp)<LineBreak/>
                📂  Open a saved playlist<LineBreak/>
                ⚙  Settings (MIDI device, channel, note, transition delay)<LineBreak/>
                📌  Toggle always-on-top<LineBreak/>
                ?  This help screen
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Reason Setup (per song file)</Run><LineBreak/>
                1. In your Reason song, create an External MIDI Instrument device.<LineBreak/>
                2. Set its MIDI output to the same device and channel configured in RLP Settings.<LineBreak/>
                3. In the sequencer, add a note on the configured trigger note number at the
                   point where the song should end.<LineBreak/>
                4. When Reason plays that note, RLP receives it and advances to the next song.
                <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">About</Run><LineBreak/>
                <Run x:Name="VersionRun"/>
                <LineBreak/>
                <Run x:Name="BuildDateRun"/>
                <LineBreak/>
                GitHub: <Hyperlink x:Name="RepoLink" RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate"
                    Foreground="#5599FF">https://github.com/t8bloom1/ReasonableLivePlayer</Hyperlink>
                <LineBreak/>
                Licensed under the MIT License.
            </TextBlock>
        </ScrollViewer>

        <Button Grid.Row="1" Content="Close" Width="80" Height="28"
                HorizontalAlignment="Right" Margin="0,12,0,0"
                Click="Close_Click" IsCancel="True"/>
    </Grid>
</Window>
